column10: A raffle will be held for the door prize at a charity fundraiser.  200 gold sponsors, 300 silver sponsors, and 400 bronze sponsors have entered the raffle.  The name of each gold sponsor was entered 3 times, the name of each silver sponsor was entered 2 times, and the name of each bronze sponsor was entered 1 time.   What is the probability that the name of a gold sponsor will be chosen?
